  <histories>
    <history>
      <header>The first steps of DNT</header>
      <text>Do Not Touch was originally a prototype conceived by Flat Pixel's co-founders and Nickelodeon in late 2017. 
      With the ARKit technology and a lot of creativity this little prototype evolved to its release on the App Store in March 2018.</text>
    </history>
    <history>
      <header>.. leading to its release </header>
      <text>In the first version of DNT, the concept was really simple : just place the button on a flat surface and touch it, and .. something happen. And the kids loved it. 
      Do Not Touch has even won its first Clio Entertainment Award for the category Virtual/Augmented Reality in 2018.</text>
    </history>
    <history>
      <header>Do Not Touch 2.0</header>
      <text>A year after, Do Not Touch was improved by addind a progression with each game completed a bunch of slime would come out of the button and used later to unlock games and skins. 
  And again a second Clio Entertainment Award has been won in 2019 in the category Virtual/Augmented Reality!</text>
    </history>
  </histories>

